oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Aerial photograph of Old Hickory, Tennessee
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This aerial photograph shows the Old Hickory village as constructed as part of the US Munitions Plant constructed between 1917-1918. The Army contracted with the DuPont Corporation to manufacture smokeless gunpowder and at the time was the largest in the world. The operation closed in 1919 but DuPont returned in 1928 and purchased the facility and village and built additional housing. The Old Hickory facility produced Rayon, Reemay, and Cellophane among other products.
